      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UPTOWN CHANCE (10) enjoyed the class drop from Menangle when he raced parked before drawing away to score by 9 metres a fortnight ago, taking his strike rate at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent. Draws on the back line this time but with even luck he can make it two on the bounce. ROCKY ROCKS (5) resumes off a string of top-two finishes including a Charlton win two back and a second behind a handy rival when last seen at Shepparton in January. Readied with two trials, winning the latest. Expecting a bright start to the campaign. ISLAND YANKEE (4) looks close to a win having placed in his last three outings and is suited returning to a circuit and distance where he has recorded a win and three placings in four attempts. SET PLAY (9) draws for a trail and was good last time out when he came from a wide barrier to finish third at this venue.",
